WEBVTT

00:00.420 --> 00:02.830
♪♪

00:03.420 --> 00:06.750
♪ ♪

00:07.710 --> 00:09.040
So, Dad,

00:09.040 --> 00:10.330
then we went to
another store,

00:10.330 --> 00:12.620
and Mom and I finally
found the perfect dress

00:12.620 --> 00:14.380
for the Father-Daughter dance
tomorrow night.

00:14.380 --> 00:16.330
I can't wait to see you in it.

00:16.330 --> 00:18.120
I wish I could've bought
it for you myself.

00:18.120 --> 00:19.330
Oh, you did!

00:19.330 --> 00:20.710
I charged it
to your credit card.

00:20.710 --> 00:22.040
Ha! Still remember
the number.

00:23.380 --> 00:24.920
Oh! Is that Dad?

00:24.920 --> 00:26.380
I wanna tell him I'm working
the photo stand at the dance!

00:26.380 --> 00:27.830
Hey, Uncle Devon,

00:27.830 --> 00:29.460
as an amateur
storm chaser,

00:29.460 --> 00:31.120
I've been tracking
a big snowstorm

00:31.120 --> 00:32.250
that's heading our way.

00:32.250 --> 00:33.330
Levi!

00:33.330 --> 00:35.250
You trying to take my
job as a weatherman?

00:35.250 --> 00:37.960
No, I just wanted to
tell you to bring a coat.

00:37.960 --> 00:40.040
Somebody's a little
insecure!

00:41.120 --> 00:42.500
Levi, I wanna show him

00:42.500 --> 00:43.750
my favorite NBA player's
gonna be there--

00:43.750 --> 00:46.460
(gasp)
Hey, Devon!
Hey! Check it out.

00:46.460 --> 00:48.460
Guess who made an edible
vegetable centerpiece

00:48.460 --> 00:49.960
for the dance, huh?

00:49.960 --> 00:51.920
I'm gonna go
with anybody but Raven.

00:51.920 --> 00:53.250
Hey, I heard that,

00:53.250 --> 00:54.290
but I'ma let you slide

00:54.290 --> 00:55.540
because your credit card
bought me

00:55.540 --> 00:57.120
these brand new boots!
(laughs)

00:57.120 --> 00:58.790
Mom! I also
wanna show him

00:58.790 --> 01:01.120
the NBA player
is Antoine Decker,

01:01.120 --> 01:03.040
AKA Antoine Dunker!

01:03.040 --> 01:05.120
-Okay!
-(gasp) Finally!

01:05.120 --> 01:07.040
Yo, Dad, check it out!
(giggle)

01:08.380 --> 01:10.120
And, the phone's dead.

01:10.120 --> 01:11.540
Oh, Booker,
cheer up.

01:11.540 --> 01:13.420
Look what your dad bought
you on his credit card.

01:13.420 --> 01:14.710
Some new sneakers!

01:17.540 --> 01:19.210
-Really, Mom?
-(gasp)

01:20.540 --> 01:22.960
He bought me a pair
of sneakers, too?

01:22.960 --> 01:24.920
Oh, that man!
He shouldn't have!

01:24.920 --> 01:26.500
He really, really
shouldn't have.

01:26.500 --> 01:27.580
♪ Ohhhh ♪

01:27.580 --> 01:29.120
-♪ Hey ♪
-♪ Yo ♪

01:29.120 --> 01:30.380
♪ Let me tell you somethin' ♪

01:30.380 --> 01:31.920
♪ Had my vision
all worked out ♪

01:31.920 --> 01:33.880
♪ But then life
had other plans ♪

01:33.880 --> 01:35.080
♪ Tell 'em, Rae ♪

01:35.080 --> 01:37.080
♪ It's crazy when things
turn upside down ♪

01:37.080 --> 01:39.540
♪ But ya gotta get up
and take that chance ♪

01:39.540 --> 01:42.210
-♪ Maybe I'm
just finding my way ♪
-♪ Learning how to fly ♪

01:42.210 --> 01:44.420
-♪ Yeah, we're gonna be okay ♪
-♪ Ya know I got you, right? ♪

01:44.420 --> 01:46.920
♪ It might be wild, but ya
know that we make it work ♪

01:46.920 --> 01:49.330
♪ We're just kids
caught up in a crazy world ♪

01:49.330 --> 01:50.790
-♪ C'mon! ♪
-♪ It's Raven's Home ♪

01:50.790 --> 01:53.460
-♪ We get loud! ♪
-♪ It's Raven's Home ♪

01:53.460 --> 01:55.120
♪ It's our crowd! ♪

01:55.120 --> 01:57.290
♪ Might be tough,
but together
we make it look good ♪

01:57.290 --> 01:59.580
♪ Down for each other
like family should ♪

01:59.580 --> 02:01.040
♪ It's Raven's Home ♪

02:01.040 --> 02:02.290
♪ When it's tough ♪

02:02.290 --> 02:03.750
♪ It's Raven's Home ♪

02:03.750 --> 02:05.040
♪ We got love ♪

02:05.040 --> 02:07.210
♪ 'Cos no matter the weather,
ya know we gon' shine ♪

02:07.210 --> 02:09.460
♪ There for each other,
ya know it's our time ♪

02:09.460 --> 02:10.920
(Raven laughing)

02:10.920 --> 02:13.210
Yep! That's us.

02:13.210 --> 02:14.290
(laughing)

02:15.710 --> 02:19.380
♪ ♪

02:19.380 --> 02:21.290
Okay, dance committee!

02:21.290 --> 02:23.710
The doors are opening,
so you can finish
your stations.

02:23.710 --> 02:25.460
Thanks for helping
with the sundae bar, Steve.

02:25.460 --> 02:26.540
You can go change.

02:28.210 --> 02:29.880
Oh, you're
wearing that? Oh...

02:29.880 --> 02:32.460
Classy! (inaudible)

02:34.000 --> 02:36.080
So?
What do you think?

02:36.080 --> 02:37.500
Think my dad'll
like it?

02:37.500 --> 02:40.040
Wow! You make
poofy look good!

02:40.040 --> 02:42.290
-Did I over-poof?
-No, you're
perfectly poof.

02:42.290 --> 02:43.580
It's a fool-poof dress.

02:43.580 --> 02:45.540
Thanks.

02:45.540 --> 02:47.380
Are you okay about your
dad not making it tonight?

02:47.380 --> 02:49.250
Yeah. I'm used to it.

02:49.250 --> 02:51.250
I'm a proud daughter
of a trucker.

02:51.250 --> 02:53.420
(giggle)
Well, you know he'd
be here if he could.

02:53.420 --> 02:54.380
Yeah. It's all good.

02:56.080 --> 02:58.170
(struggling, grunting)

02:58.170 --> 02:59.670
Oh, thanks!

02:59.670 --> 03:00.500
Hi, Booker.

03:00.500 --> 03:02.420
Oh!

03:02.420 --> 03:04.670
Hey! Sheridan Decker!

03:04.670 --> 03:06.170
Or should I say,

03:06.170 --> 03:07.670
Sheridan Dunker?

03:07.670 --> 03:09.920
My dad's the dunker.
I'm just a Decker.

03:09.920 --> 03:11.250
(laughs)

03:11.250 --> 03:12.330
(stops laughing)

03:15.120 --> 03:17.580
-What was that for? (laughs)
-Just happy to help!

03:18.750 --> 03:20.250
Daddy! Bye, Booker.

03:20.250 --> 03:21.540
(yelp)

03:21.540 --> 03:23.920
Ah, you look gorgeous!

03:25.080 --> 03:26.670
There's the Dunker.

03:26.670 --> 03:27.830
And I'm gonna get
a picture with him

03:27.830 --> 03:29.040
even if it kills me.

03:30.750 --> 03:32.500
And it just might.

03:32.500 --> 03:35.500
♪ ♪

03:38.460 --> 03:39.620
Look at us, Levi.

03:39.620 --> 03:41.460
Chilling while
everybody's at the dance.

03:41.460 --> 03:43.210
Well, we didn't
really have a choice.

03:43.210 --> 03:44.290
You're not a father,

03:44.290 --> 03:46.500
and I'm not a daughter.

03:46.500 --> 03:47.500
Although, if I were,

03:47.500 --> 03:48.920
I'd go with the name Debbie.

03:49.960 --> 03:51.790
You put a lot of thought
into that, didn't you?

03:53.620 --> 03:55.540
Well, Debs,
what you doing?

03:55.540 --> 03:57.250
Debbie. Not Debs.

03:58.710 --> 04:00.670
Anyway, I've been tracking
this winter storm,

04:00.670 --> 04:02.080
and it's a doozy.

04:02.080 --> 04:03.170
18 inches of snow,

04:03.170 --> 04:05.250
with wind gusts up
to 40 miles per hour.

04:05.250 --> 04:07.580
(laughs)
Which is why I am
staying at home,

04:07.580 --> 04:09.000
and we are watching
my favorite show,

04:09.000 --> 04:10.750
"Lady Truckers,"
starring Big Shirl.

04:10.750 --> 04:12.620
I love me some
Big Shirl.

04:12.620 --> 04:14.040
Every time
she signs off,

04:14.040 --> 04:15.580
she always goes--
(imitates radio sound)

04:15.580 --> 04:17.420
Raven and TV:
Catch you on the flip flop!

04:17.420 --> 04:19.460
-(laughs)
-(phone rings)

04:20.710 --> 04:22.290
Hey, D!
You at the dance?

04:22.290 --> 04:23.670
Rae, we got a problem.

04:23.670 --> 04:26.040
The Chicago airport is closed
'cause of the snow storm,

04:26.040 --> 04:27.290
and they had to
divert my flight.

04:27.290 --> 04:28.750
-What?
- Yeah.

04:28.750 --> 04:31.250
I'm stranded at this tiny
airport about an hour away,

04:31.250 --> 04:32.710
and all the rental cars
are gone.

04:32.710 --> 04:34.170
Devon, how did you
not see this coming?

04:34.170 --> 04:35.500
You're a weather man.

04:35.500 --> 04:38.120
How did you not see it coming?
You're a psychic.

04:38.120 --> 04:39.580
How come I didn't
see it coming?

04:39.580 --> 04:41.330
Oh, wait! I did.

04:42.750 --> 04:44.750
I feel terrible
letting Nia down.

04:44.750 --> 04:46.880
No, no, no! No one is
letting anybody down, Devon.

04:46.880 --> 04:48.250
You stay right there.

04:48.250 --> 04:50.170
I'm gonna get in
the car right now
and come get you.

04:50.170 --> 04:51.540
(sigh)
Come on, Levi.

04:51.540 --> 04:53.290
Get your coat on, alright?
We gotta go get Devon.

04:53.290 --> 04:54.670
Are you sure, Auntie Rae?

04:54.670 --> 04:56.710
It's coming down pretty hard.

04:56.710 --> 04:58.540
Oh, don't worry
about that, Levi.

04:58.540 --> 05:00.290
Little snow can't stop me.

05:01.710 --> 05:02.620
(shivering)

05:02.620 --> 05:04.170
But a lot of snow can!

05:04.170 --> 05:06.500
♪ ♪

05:06.500 --> 05:08.250
(dance music plays)

05:12.790 --> 05:14.380
Chelsea:
Okay, okay!

05:14.380 --> 05:16.830
Thank you all for coming
to our annual
Father-Daughter dance.

05:16.830 --> 05:18.250
There are snacks
and drinks,

05:18.250 --> 05:19.710
and the photo stand
is now open.

05:19.710 --> 05:21.420
-(applause)
-Oh, oh!

05:21.420 --> 05:24.670
And don't forget to partake
in our edible vegetable
centerpiece.

05:24.670 --> 05:26.170
It's delicious,

05:26.170 --> 05:27.830
and it's good
for the constitution,

05:27.830 --> 05:29.210
if you know what
I mean. (giggle)

05:31.290 --> 05:32.460
It helps you poop?

05:33.920 --> 05:36.620
Okay, then.
Party on! (laugh)

05:36.620 --> 05:38.210
(music resumes)

05:38.210 --> 05:40.250
Your photo will be ready
in a few minutes.

05:43.120 --> 05:45.620
Booker,
why do you think
Dad's not here yet?

05:45.620 --> 05:48.210
He's probably just stuck in
traffic at the airport.

05:48.210 --> 05:50.830
Yeah. Yeah, you're probably
right. Thanks, Booker.

05:50.830 --> 05:53.170
Yeah, you...
Y-you know I always
got your back.

05:55.290 --> 05:56.580
Alright, what's behind my back?

05:58.830 --> 05:59.830
The Dunker!

06:00.880 --> 06:02.580
Hey! Sorry, man,
no photos tonight.

06:02.580 --> 06:04.750
It's my daughter's dance,
and it's all about her.

06:05.880 --> 06:07.830
No photos?

06:07.830 --> 06:10.120
Why does tonight have to be
all about Sheridan?

06:11.080 --> 06:12.540
Hello?

06:12.540 --> 06:14.670
Father-Daughter dance,
it's kind of in the name.

06:15.920 --> 06:19.580
Well, you know what?
The Dunker's about
to meet the dancer.

06:19.580 --> 06:20.830
Watch me work.

06:21.830 --> 06:24.290
Dad? I'm gonna go get us
something to drink.
Be right back.

06:24.290 --> 06:25.380
Okay, baby.

06:27.250 --> 06:29.120
♪ I want you, baby ♪

06:29.120 --> 06:31.210
♪ Move soft and slow ♪

06:31.210 --> 06:32.670
♪ Come on, move it baby ♪

06:32.670 --> 06:34.750
(laughing)
Cool song, huh?

06:34.750 --> 06:36.750
(chuckle)
Yeah, sure...

06:41.580 --> 06:42.710
Oop!

06:42.710 --> 06:44.120
Oh! (laugh)

06:44.120 --> 06:46.330
Thanks! Y-you found my phone!

06:46.330 --> 06:47.920
Nice try, son.

06:47.920 --> 06:49.710
But, no photos of me.

06:49.710 --> 06:51.750
Alright, fine,
no photos of you.

06:51.750 --> 06:54.540
But how 'bout
a photo of us?

06:56.460 --> 06:58.040
Yo, yo!

06:58.040 --> 07:00.580
This next song goes out to all
the daughters in the house!

07:00.580 --> 07:02.750
Yeah, yeah, yeah!
That's right, that's right!

07:02.750 --> 07:06.290
We're on the wheels of steel,
dropping fresh beats!

07:06.290 --> 07:07.710
(Chelsea laughing)

07:07.710 --> 07:09.710
And speaking of beets, um,

07:09.710 --> 07:11.420
they're in my
vegetable centerpiece,

07:11.420 --> 07:12.880
which, uh, no one
seems to be eating?

07:12.880 --> 07:16.080
(chuckle)
Come on, party people.
Let's veggie on.

07:16.080 --> 07:17.420
(phone rings)

07:19.080 --> 07:20.880
Wassup, Ravy Rave?

07:20.880 --> 07:22.460
Don't do that.

07:23.790 --> 07:26.670
Listen, Chels,
I am freaking out.

07:26.670 --> 07:27.790
Devon just called me.

07:27.790 --> 07:29.250
He's stuck at the airport,
my car's snowed in,

07:29.250 --> 07:31.330
and I don't think he's gonna be
able to make it to the dance.

07:31.330 --> 07:33.920
Oh, no!
Nia's gonna be crushed.

07:33.920 --> 07:36.620
I know, so let's just hope that
he finds a way to get there.

07:36.620 --> 07:37.790
But don't tell Nia yet, okay?

07:37.790 --> 07:39.330
I'm so sorry,
it's so loud in here.

07:39.330 --> 07:41.120
Let me see if
I got this straight.

07:41.120 --> 07:43.170
(over microphone)
So, you don't
want me to tell Nia

07:43.170 --> 07:44.790
that her dad's not gonna
make it to the dance.

07:44.790 --> 07:46.120
Okay, I got it.

07:48.250 --> 07:49.750
(sobs)

07:49.750 --> 07:52.380
I-- I can't believe
my dad's not coming.

07:52.380 --> 07:54.920
-I...
-(shutter click)

07:54.920 --> 07:57.040
Booker,
turn off the camera!

07:57.040 --> 07:58.830
I-I don't want anyone
to see me like this.

07:58.830 --> 08:00.750
-Got it.
-(clicking)

08:02.420 --> 08:03.540
Booker:
It's stuck!

08:07.540 --> 08:08.620
My bad.

08:09.380 --> 08:11.670
♪ ♪

08:12.670 --> 08:14.500
♪ ♪

08:15.250 --> 08:17.920
Nia, I'm really sorry
Dad's not coming.

08:17.920 --> 08:20.250
Look, I know
how you feel, but...

08:20.250 --> 08:22.040
it's like with my dad.

08:22.040 --> 08:23.830
You know he'd be here
if he could.

08:24.830 --> 08:26.790
I guess you're right,
but it just...

08:26.790 --> 08:27.880
Hey!

08:27.880 --> 08:30.710
I've got an idea how to
take your mind off Dad.

08:30.710 --> 08:32.920
Why don't you help me
with the photo stand?

08:32.920 --> 08:36.290
-I don't think so.
-Come on, Nia, it'll be fun.

08:37.500 --> 08:38.580
Okay, what do you do?

08:38.580 --> 08:40.420
Well, you just talk to 'em,

08:40.420 --> 08:41.830
make 'em feel at ease,

08:41.830 --> 08:43.790
and then snap the picture.

08:43.790 --> 08:45.710
'Kay, sounds easy.

08:47.290 --> 08:48.580
Hello.

08:48.580 --> 08:50.330
Special night, huh?

08:51.210 --> 08:52.420
Fathers.

08:52.420 --> 08:54.830
Daughters!
Dancing, you know.

08:54.830 --> 08:57.210
Eating sundaes,
making memories.

08:57.210 --> 08:59.120
Well, you better enjoy this
while you can,

08:59.120 --> 09:00.580
'cause before
you know it,

09:00.580 --> 09:02.290
your dad's gonna get a job
as a weatherman,

09:02.290 --> 09:05.250
move to Dallas,
promise to show up
at your next dance,

09:05.250 --> 09:07.000
get snowed in,
and never show up.

09:07.000 --> 09:08.040
Say, "Cheese!"

09:10.500 --> 09:12.080
Okay, well...

09:12.080 --> 09:13.920
that was fun!

09:13.920 --> 09:16.330
Uh, why don't you
see if Tess

09:16.330 --> 09:18.040
needs any help
at the DJ booth.

09:18.040 --> 09:19.710
Yeah! I could totally--

09:19.710 --> 09:21.500
Yeah! Yeah!
Yeah! Yes!

09:22.920 --> 09:24.750
♪ ♪

09:25.920 --> 09:27.670
(deep voice)
Nia, your father
has arrived.

09:27.670 --> 09:29.580
May I have this da--
No, that's too much.

09:31.790 --> 09:33.330
Nia...

09:33.330 --> 09:34.540
I'm your daddy.

09:38.380 --> 09:40.790
No?
I'm trying to pass as a dad,

09:40.790 --> 09:42.880
just in case
Devon can't make it.
Is the rose too much?

09:42.880 --> 09:45.210
The rose is the only thing
that works.

09:45.210 --> 09:46.790
(door knocking)

09:46.790 --> 09:47.830
I'll get it.

09:51.120 --> 09:53.500
-Hi, Mr. O'Malley!
-Hey, Levi!

09:53.500 --> 09:55.750
-Rae!
-Jimmy! How you doing?

09:55.750 --> 09:58.170
I'm so glad to see you.
Tess said you weren't gonna
make it to the dance.

09:58.170 --> 10:00.170
I cut my truck route short,
so I could surprise her.

10:01.790 --> 10:03.920
Is there something different
about you, Rae?

10:05.120 --> 10:07.500
-No.
-Change your hair?

10:08.290 --> 10:09.670
No.

10:09.670 --> 10:11.880
She thinks she can pass
as a dad.

10:11.880 --> 10:13.330
Well, I'm trying!

10:13.330 --> 10:14.960
At least I bought this
easy-off glue.

10:14.960 --> 10:17.210
-Ow! Whoopi--
-(ripping)

10:17.210 --> 10:18.880
Goldberg, that hurt!

10:19.920 --> 10:21.580
Yah!

10:21.580 --> 10:22.880
So, where's Devon?

10:22.880 --> 10:25.040
Oh, he got snowed in
at the airport.

10:25.040 --> 10:27.040
Ah, that's too bad.
I was hoping he'd be there.

10:27.040 --> 10:27.920
Anyway, Rae,
I just came by

10:27.920 --> 10:29.460
to see if you could
keep an eye on my rig.

10:29.460 --> 10:31.120
I got it parked right
out your window.

10:31.120 --> 10:33.960
Hey! So, how does your rig
handle in the pow-pow?

10:33.960 --> 10:35.540
You know that's trucker talk
for snow?

10:35.540 --> 10:36.960
-It is?
-Mm-hmm.

10:36.960 --> 10:38.210
Well, we just call it snow.

10:38.210 --> 10:40.540
But the truck handles
like a 12-ton dream.

10:47.540 --> 10:49.170
Woo, Jimmy was right!

10:49.170 --> 10:51.670
She handles
like a 12-ton dream.

10:52.330 --> 10:54.330
Nothing like the open road,
huh, Levi?

10:54.330 --> 10:56.750
Wow, I'm really impressed
with how you're handling

10:56.750 --> 10:58.960
this rig in these conditions,
Auntie Rae.

10:58.960 --> 11:00.040
Thank you. (laughs)

11:00.040 --> 11:02.040
You can just
call me Big Shirl.

11:03.880 --> 11:06.040
Well, Big Shirl better put her
big foot on the gas

11:06.040 --> 11:07.540
if we wanna
pick up Devon in time.

11:07.540 --> 11:09.080
Copy that! Pedal to the metal!

11:09.080 --> 11:10.210
Catch you on the flip flop!

11:10.210 --> 11:11.830
(honks horn)

11:11.830 --> 11:12.920
(engine revs)

11:12.920 --> 11:15.460
Nothing can stop us now.

11:15.460 --> 11:17.380
(police siren)

11:20.170 --> 11:20.960
(brakes squeal)

11:23.210 --> 11:25.250
♪ ♪

11:25.250 --> 11:26.920
(funky music playing)

11:29.380 --> 11:30.710
You takin' any requests?

11:30.710 --> 11:32.960
Hey, do I come to your job
and tell you what to--

11:32.960 --> 11:35.120
-(gasp) Dad!
-Hey, sweetie!

11:35.120 --> 11:37.710
-Surprise!
-Man, I thought
you weren't coming.

11:37.710 --> 11:40.170
How could I ever
disappoint that face?

11:40.170 --> 11:43.120
I just wanna squeeze
those cheeks.

11:43.120 --> 11:44.960
Okay, time's up.

11:44.960 --> 11:46.960
Hey! It's your own fault
for having that face.

11:46.960 --> 11:48.580
Whoa, Nia!

11:48.580 --> 11:49.710
Look at you!

11:49.710 --> 11:51.040
Hi, Mr. O'Malley.

11:51.040 --> 11:53.330
Now, I have two princesses
to dance with.

11:53.330 --> 11:55.120
If your highnesses
will excuse me,

11:55.120 --> 11:57.920
I gotta go fill up on some
dancing fuel first.

11:59.250 --> 12:01.710
Hey! And stay away
from the dairy!

12:01.710 --> 12:03.000
You know how you get!

12:04.290 --> 12:06.960
What? I gotta ride home
with him.

12:06.960 --> 12:09.830
Tess, that's really
sweet of your dad offering
to dance with me,

12:09.830 --> 12:12.000
but this is your
night together.

12:12.000 --> 12:14.170
You know, this dress
was bought to be danced in,

12:14.170 --> 12:16.120
be a shame
to let it go to waste.

12:16.120 --> 12:17.210
Wanna switch?

12:17.210 --> 12:19.000
Eh, you think I could
pull off the poof?

12:19.000 --> 12:21.120
Hey, if your dad can
pull off a toupee,

12:21.120 --> 12:22.420
you can pull off the poof.

12:22.420 --> 12:24.710
Shhh!
He thinks nobody knows.

12:27.040 --> 12:30.540
♪ ♪

12:31.920 --> 12:33.330
Auntie Rae, what are we
gonna do now?

12:33.330 --> 12:35.120
Calm down,
sweetheart, calm down.
You know what?

12:35.120 --> 12:37.500
This, this is a perfect
learning lesson, alright?

12:37.500 --> 12:40.000
This is what happens
when the cops pull you over.

12:40.000 --> 12:41.420
You stay calm, alright?

12:41.420 --> 12:44.000
You put your hands
on the dash.
Leave them there.

12:44.000 --> 12:45.250
Alright. (clears throat)

12:45.250 --> 12:48.040
You tell the truth, cause
we have nothing to hide.
Yeah?

12:48.040 --> 12:49.790
(footsteps approaching)

12:50.830 --> 12:54.250
-(window crank rattling)
-License and
registration.

12:54.250 --> 12:56.120
Yes, yes. Um, ma'am.

12:56.120 --> 12:59.250
See? Calm, and collected.
There you go.

13:00.120 --> 13:01.710
Huh.

13:01.710 --> 13:04.880
It says here,
this rig is registered
to a James O'Malley.

13:04.880 --> 13:06.120
So, who are you?

13:06.120 --> 13:08.210
Huh? I'm Jimmy's
trucker friend.

13:08.210 --> 13:10.080
Uh, he-- he let me
borrow his rig,

13:10.080 --> 13:12.080
and he, and he also let me
borrow this mustache.

13:12.080 --> 13:14.620
See? 'Cause we're friends of
Jimmy's, and that's what
truckers do.

13:14.620 --> 13:16.250
Truckers truck together.

13:16.250 --> 13:18.580
-(honks horn)
-I don't know why
I can't stop.

13:19.580 --> 13:23.210
Okay, you two do not look like
any truckers I've ever seen.
What--

13:23.210 --> 13:25.460
-(ripping)
-Ella Fitzgerald!

13:25.460 --> 13:27.120
-Ella Fitzgerald?
-Yeah.

13:27.120 --> 13:30.750
It says here,
you're Raven Baxter.
So, which is it?

13:30.750 --> 13:32.830
Um, actually,
my name's Raven Baxter,

13:32.830 --> 13:35.290
but around these parts,
they call me, uh...

13:35.290 --> 13:36.330
They call me Big Rae.

13:37.620 --> 13:39.290
And this here--
this here is...

13:39.290 --> 13:41.710
-This here's Little Deb.
-It's Debbie!

13:44.210 --> 13:47.290
Okay, so Big Rae,
and Little Debbie, huh?

13:47.290 --> 13:48.830
Yeah! That's right!
That's right.

13:48.830 --> 13:50.960
Breaker breaker 10-17,
on the seven-tile!

13:50.960 --> 13:53.290
We got hit in the double zone
in the hydro-pipe--

13:53.290 --> 13:54.830
dro-planing.

13:54.830 --> 13:58.380
We're here with... the cop from
the seven. We... trucker!

13:58.380 --> 13:59.960
(honks horn)

14:01.620 --> 14:04.040
(sigh)
Okay, you know?
I've heard enough.

14:04.040 --> 14:06.120
You got nothing
on me, copper!

14:06.120 --> 14:08.210
-I'm making a run for it.
-No! No, Debbie!

14:08.210 --> 14:10.080
No Debbie!
Come on, get--
(indistinct)

14:11.120 --> 14:12.670
Debbie! Get...

14:12.670 --> 14:13.830
Get back!

14:14.830 --> 14:16.330
Look, you two!

14:16.330 --> 14:17.620
I don't know
what you're up to,

14:17.620 --> 14:19.380
but it's freezing out here!

14:19.380 --> 14:20.710
My nose hairs
are frozen,

14:20.710 --> 14:22.830
and they're starting to whistle,
"Chattanooga Choo Choo!"

14:22.830 --> 14:24.170
Oh, I like that song.

14:25.460 --> 14:27.380
-So, I'm gonna let you off
with a warning.
-Okay.

14:27.380 --> 14:29.250
Your license checks out,

14:29.250 --> 14:30.790
but I don't
wanna see you again.

14:30.790 --> 14:33.210
Okay. Alright. Uh, copy that.
Catch you on the flip flop.

14:33.210 --> 14:34.960
(honks horn)

14:34.960 --> 14:36.040
Don't do that again!

14:36.040 --> 14:37.580
I'm sorry! Okay!
Copy that, copy that!

14:37.580 --> 14:39.330
Hands on the dash!

14:40.580 --> 14:44.580
♪ ♪

14:44.580 --> 14:45.920
(dancing music plays)

14:52.290 --> 14:54.210
Wow...

14:54.210 --> 14:55.500
Look at my girl.

14:55.500 --> 14:57.210
All poofed up.

14:57.210 --> 14:59.330
Guess that makes me
Poof Daddy.

15:00.380 --> 15:02.290
Dad?
More dancey, less talky.

15:04.380 --> 15:05.500
I take that back.

15:05.500 --> 15:07.330
More talky, less dancey.

15:12.330 --> 15:14.880
Thanks, Booker,
I love cherries.
How'd you know?

15:14.880 --> 15:17.250
Eh, I know things.

15:17.250 --> 15:19.580
Like, maybe,
you wanna dance with me?

15:19.580 --> 15:21.120
Sure!

15:22.830 --> 15:24.120
(strained laugh)

15:25.250 --> 15:27.500
I, uh, I also knew
you were gonna do that!

15:33.620 --> 15:35.290
Ha ha, look at us!

15:35.290 --> 15:38.210
Dancing at a
Father Daughter dance.

15:38.210 --> 15:40.170
Hope no one thinks
I'm your father.

15:41.420 --> 15:43.210
Hey, speaking of
your father...

15:44.120 --> 15:45.210
(slow, downbeat music)

15:46.620 --> 15:48.750
Whoa, this DJ is terrible.

15:48.750 --> 15:50.960
Ha, awful, right?

15:50.960 --> 15:52.210
I'll be right back.

15:53.460 --> 15:54.620
Nia! What're you doing?

15:54.620 --> 15:57.330
Uh, what do you mean?
I'm up here crushing it.

15:57.330 --> 16:00.250
Crushing what?
These people's spirits?

16:03.120 --> 16:04.790
Hey, look,
I'm sorry, Booker.

16:04.790 --> 16:06.790
I've been trying my best
to pretend

16:06.790 --> 16:08.830
I'm not upset that Dad's not
coming, but...

16:10.460 --> 16:12.250
I can't. I'm really
disappointed.

16:16.580 --> 16:17.670
(whooshing)

16:22.380 --> 16:24.000
(whooshing)

16:25.790 --> 16:28.290
Well, you don't have to be
disappointed anymore.

16:28.290 --> 16:30.880
I just had a vision.
I saw you and Dad dancing!

16:30.880 --> 16:32.330
Which means he makes it!

16:32.330 --> 16:33.790
Wait, really?
Are you sure?

16:33.790 --> 16:35.710
Yeah, you were even
wearing your dress...

16:36.880 --> 16:38.040
that you're not wearing.

16:38.040 --> 16:39.290
Why aren't you wearing
your dress?

16:39.290 --> 16:40.880
I let Tess wear it.

16:41.580 --> 16:43.380
Well, if you want my vision
to come true,

16:43.380 --> 16:44.380
you better get it back.

16:47.500 --> 16:49.500
(dancing music comes back)

16:51.000 --> 16:54.250
Oh, Tess! You look so cute
dancing in that dress.

16:54.250 --> 16:56.960
Thanks! I think
I'm really pulling it off.

16:56.960 --> 16:58.420
Yeah.
Speaking of which...

17:02.500 --> 17:04.500
Wow, Booker,
you can really dance.

17:04.500 --> 17:06.830
-So can you!
-Really? I hope so.

17:06.830 --> 17:08.040
Cause I don't
have much practice.

17:08.040 --> 17:09.330
I don't get asked
to dance a lot.

17:09.330 --> 17:11.040
What? Why not?

17:11.040 --> 17:13.620
Probably because I'm so much
taller than boys my age.

17:13.620 --> 17:16.120
You are?
I didn't even notice.

17:16.120 --> 17:17.290
You're so funny.

17:18.330 --> 17:19.380
(painful laugh)

17:22.960 --> 17:24.120
-Hey, Booker.
-Yeah.

17:24.120 --> 17:25.420
Quick question.

17:26.420 --> 17:28.540
In your vision, when did you
see Dad come in here?

17:28.540 --> 17:29.380
Cause it's getting
pretty late.

17:29.380 --> 17:31.250
Don't worry,
he's gonna be here.

17:31.250 --> 17:32.330
Trust in the vision.

17:32.330 --> 17:34.420
Now, move out of the way.

17:34.420 --> 17:36.000
-For what?
-For this.

17:36.000 --> 17:37.380
Ow!

17:41.750 --> 17:44.790
You know, usually
guys are only nice to me
to get to my dad.

17:44.790 --> 17:47.380
What?
Who does that?

17:47.380 --> 17:50.380
I get it though.
People get excited
meeting an all-star

17:50.380 --> 17:51.920
who averages
29 points a game.

17:51.920 --> 17:54.710
Uh, it's 30,
with 12 assists

17:54.710 --> 17:56.380
and 92 percent
from the stripe.

17:56.380 --> 17:58.500
But, (laughs)
who's counting, right?

17:58.500 --> 18:00.000
So...

18:00.000 --> 18:01.290
how long has your dad
been your dad?

18:04.460 --> 18:06.750
Have you only been nice to me
to get to my father?

18:07.580 --> 18:09.710
No!
I, I mean, yeah,

18:09.710 --> 18:11.040
I-I wanted
a picture, but--

18:11.040 --> 18:13.080
I knew it!

18:13.080 --> 18:14.920
You're just like
everyone else!

18:14.920 --> 18:16.920
You didn't wanna hang out
with Sheridan Decker.

18:16.920 --> 18:19.580
You wanted to hang out
with Antoine Decker.

18:19.580 --> 18:21.120
Well, maybe
he'll dance with you.

18:21.120 --> 18:22.250
You think he would?

18:22.250 --> 18:23.580
(scoff)

18:23.580 --> 18:26.000
♪ ♪

18:27.040 --> 18:28.540
♪ ♪

18:30.210 --> 18:32.710
Breaker 1-9, breaker 1-9.
Little Debbie here.

18:32.710 --> 18:35.460
Just picked up Big Daddy, and
are heading back to Chi-Town.

18:35.460 --> 18:37.420
Anybody go their ears on?

18:37.420 --> 18:39.210
You know
that's not on, right?

18:39.210 --> 18:42.500
Well, it's better than
listening to you say,

18:42.500 --> 18:43.580
"Are we there yet?"

18:43.580 --> 18:44.750
(laugh)

18:44.750 --> 18:47.080
Well, are we there yet, Rae?

18:47.080 --> 18:49.000
Okay, calm down,
Devon, alright?

18:49.000 --> 18:51.170
We are going to make it
to the dance on time.

18:51.170 --> 18:53.540
This rig plows
through snow.

18:54.710 --> 18:55.790
But not ice!

18:55.790 --> 18:57.420
-(all scream)
-(tires squeal)

19:00.960 --> 19:02.420
Okay, everybody,
calm down!

19:02.420 --> 19:03.920
It is under control!

19:03.920 --> 19:05.500
Alright?
I got this! (laugh)

19:05.500 --> 19:07.120
Dance, here we come!

19:07.120 --> 19:09.500
-(siren)
-Oh, snap!

19:12.380 --> 19:13.960
♪ ♪

19:13.960 --> 19:15.500
Oh, wow!

19:15.500 --> 19:17.710
Well, I don't know
if I'm seeing spots,

19:17.710 --> 19:20.420
but I can't tell who's who.
(laugh) Here you go.

19:22.580 --> 19:24.330
Meow!

19:24.330 --> 19:26.500
Hey, thanks for covering
my stand, Aunt Chelsea.

19:26.500 --> 19:27.580
Oh, no problem.

19:27.580 --> 19:29.000
Did you have fun
dancing with Sheridan?

19:30.080 --> 19:32.040
I kinda blew it.

19:32.040 --> 19:33.330
She's pretty mad at me.

19:33.330 --> 19:34.830
She didn't even punch me
in the arm.

19:34.830 --> 19:37.670
She's been punching you
in the arm?

19:37.670 --> 19:40.250
You know what that means?
She likes you.

19:40.250 --> 19:43.250
-She... likes me?
-Yeah.

19:43.250 --> 19:45.500
Oh, no.
That makes this
even worse.

19:45.500 --> 19:48.460
I just wanted a picture with
Antoine Decker so bad,

19:48.460 --> 19:50.540
I didn't even realize
she was crushing on me.

19:52.040 --> 19:53.170
What do I do?

19:53.170 --> 19:54.540
Now, look, Booker.

19:54.540 --> 19:57.380
If there's one thing girls
appreciate, it's honesty.

19:57.380 --> 19:59.920
So just explain yourself
and apologize.

19:59.920 --> 20:01.580
-You're right.
-Yeah.

20:01.580 --> 20:03.580
I-I owe it to her.

20:03.580 --> 20:06.380
-Thanks, Aunt Chelsea.
-Oh, honey, don't thank me.
Just...

20:06.380 --> 20:08.960
eat some of my
centerpiece, huh?
Make me look good.

20:08.960 --> 20:10.040
Honestly?

20:10.040 --> 20:11.580
-It's not gonna happen.
-Oh come on, honey.

20:11.580 --> 20:13.500
-Please? Oh, come on.
-No, no, no.

20:13.500 --> 20:16.000
♪ ♪

20:16.000 --> 20:18.500
Well, looks like this party's
gotten bigger

20:18.500 --> 20:20.120
since the last time
I saw you.

20:20.120 --> 20:23.540
Don't tell me.
Big Rae, Little Debbie,
and--

20:23.540 --> 20:26.000
(gasp)
O-M-G.

20:26.000 --> 20:27.420
Devon Carter?

20:27.420 --> 20:29.120
Dallas Action News
weatherman?

20:29.120 --> 20:31.580
(giggles)
I used to live in Dallas.

20:31.580 --> 20:33.170
I'm a really big fan.
(giggle)

20:33.170 --> 20:34.710
(whispers)
Turn on the charm,
turn on the charm.

20:36.500 --> 20:38.620
So... come here often?

20:41.040 --> 20:42.670
Not you.

20:42.670 --> 20:45.920
♪ ♪

20:50.620 --> 20:53.960
Tess... Tess, please hold off
on playing the final song.

20:53.960 --> 20:56.710
I know my dad's gonna be here.
What about Booker's vision?

20:56.710 --> 20:59.380
Nia! I can't hold off
any longer.

20:59.380 --> 21:01.540
After this song, I'm gonna
have to play it.

21:01.540 --> 21:03.880
(music continues)

21:06.500 --> 21:07.580
(shutter clicks)

21:08.620 --> 21:10.210
Ah. Uh, hey, Sheridan.

21:10.210 --> 21:13.210
Booker, my dad and I
would like a picture, please.

21:13.210 --> 21:15.580
Uh, y-y-yeah. Sure.

21:15.580 --> 21:17.330
Hey...

21:18.420 --> 21:19.750
Sheridan, can I talk to you
for a minute?

21:19.750 --> 21:21.170
What do you want?

21:22.580 --> 21:24.460
I-I just wanna
apologize for the way

21:24.460 --> 21:25.710
I was treating you
tonight.

21:25.710 --> 21:27.420
I-I never should've
tried to use you

21:27.420 --> 21:29.210
to get a pic
with your dad.

21:29.210 --> 21:30.710
It was selfish,

21:30.710 --> 21:32.670
it was mean, and...

21:32.670 --> 21:33.670
you deserve better.

21:33.670 --> 21:35.670
Yeah. You're right, I do.

21:35.670 --> 21:37.080
I...

21:37.080 --> 21:39.670
I just wish I'd gotten to
know you for you because...

21:41.120 --> 21:42.500
you seem pretty cool.

21:43.580 --> 21:45.620
Thanks.

21:45.620 --> 21:47.500
(music continues)

21:49.500 --> 21:50.750
'Kay.

21:53.000 --> 21:54.170
(laughs)

22:00.540 --> 22:01.750
(shutter snaps)

22:01.750 --> 22:04.830
Alright. Uh, your photo
will be ready soon.

22:04.830 --> 22:07.250
Wait, Dad. One more pic?

22:08.290 --> 22:09.620
Booker? You wanna
get in this one?

22:10.670 --> 22:13.290
Me? With you guys?

22:13.290 --> 22:14.750
(laughing) Sure!

22:19.750 --> 22:21.250
Wait, who's gonna
take the picture?

22:21.250 --> 22:24.460
(shouting)
Aunt Chelsea! Hurry!

22:26.710 --> 22:29.580
Okay, dads!
Pick up a rose
for your daughter.

22:29.580 --> 22:32.880
It is time for the final
father daughter dance.

22:34.790 --> 22:36.000
(quietly) Sorry.

22:36.000 --> 22:37.540
(slow dance music)

22:46.420 --> 22:47.710
Well, that's it.

22:49.120 --> 22:51.250
The dance is over,
and Dad's not here.

22:51.250 --> 22:53.830
I don't understand.

22:53.830 --> 22:55.830
I had a vision of you
and Dad dancing.

22:57.750 --> 22:59.620
I guess I got it wrong.

22:59.620 --> 23:01.460
Just wish you weren't
wrong tonight.

23:01.460 --> 23:03.460
♪ A sea of endless faces ♪

23:03.460 --> 23:06.790
♪ In a world
of constant changes ♪

23:06.790 --> 23:10.960
♪ There's always been someone
that's by my side ♪

23:10.960 --> 23:13.080
♪ ♪

23:16.000 --> 23:17.790
Well, I've had better nights.

23:17.790 --> 23:21.040
♪ I'll always by there ♪

23:21.040 --> 23:22.790
Mom?

23:22.790 --> 23:23.920
Mom, what's going on?

23:23.920 --> 23:25.830
Your night's
not over yet, baby.

23:26.710 --> 23:28.330
May I have this dance?

23:29.670 --> 23:31.000
Oh, Dad!

23:31.000 --> 23:33.580
♪ I'll always be there ♪

23:33.580 --> 23:37.000
♪ When the world is spinning
or moving slow ♪

23:37.000 --> 23:41.080
♪ Whatever trouble
is all your own ♪

23:41.080 --> 23:42.750
Well,

23:42.750 --> 23:44.710
I guess my vision
wasn't wrong after all.

23:44.710 --> 23:49.000
♪ Always be there ♪

23:50.330 --> 23:51.710
So, Dad,

23:51.710 --> 23:53.500
check out what I got
at the dance.

23:54.920 --> 23:56.880
-Is that Antoine Dunker?
-And me!

23:56.880 --> 23:58.880
-Where?
-Yeah, I don't see you.

23:58.880 --> 24:00.960
No, I-I'm right there.

24:00.960 --> 24:02.460
Yeah. I'm the hair.

24:03.960 --> 24:05.670
♪ ♪
